https://leetcode.com/problems/combination-sum/description/

QUESTION:
Input: candidates = [2,3,6,7], target = 7
Output: [[2,2,3],[7]]

Input: candidates = [2,3,5], target = 8
Output: [[2,2,2,2],[2,3,3],[3,5]]
SOLUTION:
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
TIME  COMPLEXITY:O(2^Target)
SPACE COMPLEXITY:O(Target)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Since repetition is allowed,you can backtrack 
Start with empty:
[] sum=0

Pick 2:
[2] sum=2
[2,2] sum=4
[2,2,2] sum=6

→ Try adding 2 → [2,2,2,2] sum=8 ❌ (backtrack)
→ Try adding 3 → [2,2,3] sum=7 ✅ (add to result)
→ Try adding 6/7 → exceeds ❌

Backtrack:
[2,2,2] → [2,2]

From [2,2]:
→ Try 6 → [2,2,6] = 10 ❌
→ Try 7 → [2,2,7] = 11 ❌

Backtrack:
[2,2] → [2]

From [2]:
→ Try 3 → [2,3] sum=5
    → Try 3 → [2,3,3] = 8 ❌
    → Try 6/7 → ❌
→ Try 6 → [2,6] = 8 ❌
→ Try 7 → [2,7] = 9 ❌

Backtrack:
[2] → []

Pick 3:
[3] sum=3
[3,3] sum=6
→ Try 3 → [3,3,3] = 9 ❌
→ Try 6/7 → ❌

Backtrack:
[3,3] → [3] → []

Pick 6:
[6] sum=6
→ Try 6 → 12 ❌
→ Try 7 → 13 ❌

Backtrack:
[6] → []

Pick 7:
[7] sum=7 ✅ (add to result)

Final Result:
[[2,2,3], [7]]
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
CODE:

class Solution {
    List<List<Integer>>ar=new ArrayList<>();
    public List<List<Integer>> combinationSum(int[] candidates, int target) {
        backtrack(candidates,target,0,0,new ArrayList<Integer>());
        return ar;
    }
    public void backtrack(int[] candidates,int target,int sum,int index,ArrayList<Integer>temp){
        if(target==sum){
            ar.add(new ArrayList<>(temp));
        }
        if(sum>target)return;
        for(int i=index;i<candidates.length;i++){
            temp.add(candidates[i]);
            backtrack(candidates,target,sum+candidates[i],i,temp);
            temp.remove(temp.size()-1);
        }
    }
}
